6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Pipefy and Zoho Flow share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Api Connections, Scheduling, Conditional Logic. Where Pipefy pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Ai Actions, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Zoho Flow uniquely offers Code Support, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Pipefy holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Zoho Flow scores 6/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Pipefy and Zoho Flow offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Pipefy's free tier and Zoho Flow's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
