a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Pipefy is best suited for HR teams, procurement, service management, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Zoho Flow, meanwhile, shines for Zoho users, small businesses, budget conscious teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2014, Pipefy describes itself as \"AI-enhanced business process automation with customizable workflows.\" Zoho Flow, established in 1996, positions itself as \"Integration platform connecting Zoho and third-party apps with automated workflows.\" With 18 years between them, Zoho Flow brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Pipefy offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Pipefy** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Zoho Flow is a poor choice — far from it. Zoho Flow excels in its own right, particularly for Zoho users and small businesses.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent pipe/kanban workflow model, go with Pipefy. If excellent value within zoho ecosystem matters more to you, Zoho Flow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
